"title": "5073: Aaron, as model priest",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5073: aaron, as model priest",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Aaron was made high priest and charged with the responsibility of making offerings for the sins of the people and ensuring that the LORD was worshipped in the proper manner. His priesthood was to pass to his descendants, thus ensuring its continuity.</p>\n<h2>Aaron was high priest</h2>\n<h3>His call to the priesthood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:10\">NUM 3:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:1\">EXO 28:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:6\">1SA 12:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps99:6\">PSA 99:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:4\">HEB 5:4</a></p>\n<h3>His anointing, ordination and consecration</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:41\">EXO 28:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:7-Exod29:9\">EXO 29:7–29:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:12\">LEV 8:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:14\">LEV 8:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:22\">LEV 8:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:27\">LEV 8:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:30\">LEV 8:30</a></p>\n<h3>His priestly garments</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:2\">EXO 28:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:4\">EXO 28:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:36\">EXO 28:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:42\">EXO 28:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:7-Lev8:9\">LEV 8:7–8:9</a></p>\n<h3>The significance of the priestly garments</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:9-Exod28:12\">EXO 28:9–28:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:30\">EXO 28:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:34-Exod28:35\">EXO 28:34–28:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:36-Exod28:38\">EXO 28:36–28:38</a></p>\n<h3>Skilled craftsmen were employed in the making of the priestly garments</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:6\">EXO 31:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:10\">EXO 31:10</a></p>\n<h3>Fellow Levites were to help Aaron in ministry</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:2\">NUM 18:2</a></p>\n<h2>Aaron's priestly privileges</h2>\n<h3>In sacrificial offerings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:27-Exod29:28\">EXO 29:27–29:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:32-Exod29:33\">EXO 29:32–29:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:3\">LEV 2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:35-Lev7:36\">LEV 7:35–7:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:8-Num18:9\">NUM 18:8–18:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:11-Num18:13\">NUM 18:11–18:13</a></p>\n<h3>In tithes</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:28\">NUM 18:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:37\">NEH 10:37</a></p>\n<h3>In cities allotted to his descendants</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh21:19\">JOS 21:19</a></p>\n<h2>Aaron's priestly responsibilities</h2>\n<h3>Respect for the holiness of the LORD and his sanctuary</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:3\">LEV 10:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:1-Lev10:2\">LEV 10:1–10:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:1-Lev22:2\">LEV 22:1–22:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:7\">NUM 18:7</a></p>\n<h3>Keeping ritually clean</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:10-Lev21:12\">LEV 21:10–21:12</a></p>\n<h3>Tending the lamps in the Tent of Meeting</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod27:21\">EXO 27:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:7\">EXO 30:7</a></p>\n<h3>Obeying the LORD's commands about sacrificial ritual and offerings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:8-Lev6:9\">LEV 6:8–6:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:14\">LEV 6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:24-Lev6:25\">LEV 6:24–6:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:1\">LEV 7:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:11\">LEV 7:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:37\">LEV 7:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev9:22\">LEV 9:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:8\">NUM 18:8</a></p>\n<h3>Taking responsibility for the offences against the sanctuary and the priesthood</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:1\">NUM 18:1</a></p>\n<h2>The future of Aaron's priesthood</h2>\n<h3>The LORD's requirements are to stand for all time</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:8\">EXO 30:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:36\">LEV 7:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:3\">LEV 22:3</a></p>\n<h3>The priesthood continues through Aaron's descendants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:28\">NUM 20:28</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Aaron's priesthood compared with Melchizedek's</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:11\">HEB 7:11</a></p>",
